# ─── Build-time env (committed template) ────────────────────────────────────
# Copy to .env (and optionally .env.production / .env.staging / .env.development).
# build.sh loads the environment-specific file, falling back to .env, and exports
# every key into process.env. The backend (esbuild) bakes in all of them; the
# webview (vite) bakes in only VITE_ / CCG_PUBLIC_ prefixed keys.
#
# Prefix presence = browser exposure: prefixed values ship to end-user browsers,
# so never give a secret a VITE_ / CCG_PUBLIC_ prefix.
#
# See docs/build-env-injection.md for the full model.

# Telemetry (Rybbit) API key — backend only (unprefixed), baked in at build time.
CCG_RYBBIT_API_KEY=

# Example public webview flag (prefixed → exposed to the browser):
# CCG_PUBLIC_EXAMPLE_FLAG=true
